ication style could be refined, the combination of proven reliability, crisis composure, and relevant technical skills makes B the most suitable for the high\u2011responsibility, long\u2011distance pilot position.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}", "thoughts": "We need to produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE and METADATA_JSON. We need to discuss candidate evaluation based on our known info. We have full list of attributes for all candidates. So we can evaluate.\n\nWe must not invent. Use given attributes.\n\nList positives and negatives:\n\nCandidate A: positives: anticipate dangerous situations, see complex connections, excellent spatial vision, very good leadership qualities. Negatives: unfriendly, eats unhealthily.\n\nCandidate B: positives: keeps calm in a crisis, 100% reliable, good at assessing weather conditions, excellent computer skills. Negatives: regarded as pretentious, sometimes adopts wrong tone when communicating.\n\nCandidate C: positives: can make correct decisions quickly, puts concern for others above everything, excellent attention skills. Negatives: difficulty communicating ideas, regarded as egocentric, not very willing to further his education.\n\nCandidate D: positives: responds to unexpected events adequately, can concentrate very well, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously. Negatives: considered moody, regarded as a loner.\n\nNow evaluate for long-distance pilot: reliability, technical competence, calm under pressure, teamwork/communication, decision-making, long-term suitability.\n\nReliability: B (100% reliable), D (takes responsibility seriously), A? not mentioned, C? not mentioned.\n\nTechnical competence: A (spatial vision, complex connections), B (weather assessment, computer skills), D (problem solving, concentration), C (attention skills, quick decisions).\n\nCalm under pressure: B (keeps calm in crisis), D (responds adequately to unexpected), A? anticipate dangerous, but not calm, C? q